  "chapter": 2,
  "section": 5,
  "book": "algebra-1",
  "epigraph": {
    "text": "Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as \nworking for the Lord, not for human masters.",
    "reference": "Colossians 3:23",
    "quote": "The only way to learn mathematics is to do mathematics.",
    "quoteAuthor": "Paul Halmos"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "{The only way to learn mathematics is to do mathematics.}{Paul Halmos}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This chapter introduced you to the foundational language of algebra: \nvariables, expressions, and the operations we perform on them. These \nconcepts form the vocabulary and grammar you will use throughout your \nstudy of mathematics."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts Summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Vocabulary Review"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Match each term with its definition."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "",
        "**Term**",
        "",
        "**Definition**"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "1.",
          "Variable",
          "A.",
          "A mathematical phrase with variables, numbers, and operations"
        ],
        [
          "2.",
          "Coefficient",
          "B.",
          "A letter that represents a number"
        ],
        [
          "3.",
          "Constant",
          "C.",
          "Terms with the same variable parts and exponents"
        ],
        [
          "4.",
          "Algebraic expression",
          "D.",
          "A term with no variable"
        ],
        [
          "5.",
          "Like terms",
          "E.",
          "The numerical factor of a term"
        ],
        [
          "6.",
          "Evaluate",
          "F.",
          "To substitute values and calculate the result"
        ],
        [
          "7.",
          "Simplify",
          "G.",
          "$a(b + c) = ab + ac$"
        ],
        [
          "8.",
          "Distributive property",
          "H.",
          "To combine like terms and remove parentheses"
        ]
      ],
      "alignment": [
        "center",
        "left",
        "center",
        "center"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "*Answers: 1-B, 2-E, 3-D, 4-A, 5-C, 6-F, 7-H, 8-G*"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chapter Review Exercises"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 2.1: Variables and Algebraic Expressions**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Identify each as an expression or an equation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$4x + 7$",
        "$3y - 5 = 10$",
        "$\\dfrac{n}{2} + 8$",
        "$2m = 14$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For the expression $6x^2 - 4x + 9$, identify:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "the number of terms",
        "the coefficient of $x^2$",
        "the coefficient of $x$",
        "the constant term"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Determine whether each pair consists of like terms."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$5x^2$ and $-2x^2$",
        "$3xy$ and $7x$",
        "$9$ and $-4$",
        "$4ab^2$ and $4a^2b$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Write an algebraic expression for each phrase."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "A number $n$ increased by $7$",
        "The product of $5$ and a number $x$",
        "Twice a number $y$, decreased by $3$",
        "The quotient of $m$ and $6$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 2.2: Translating Verbal Expressions**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Translate each phrase into an algebraic expression."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Eight more than a number $p$",
        "Twelve less than a number $q$",
        "The sum of twice $r$ and $5$",
        "Three times the quantity $s$ minus $4$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Translate each phrase."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "The difference of $x$ and $9$",
        "Seven subtracted from $y$",
        "One-half of the sum of $n$ and $6$",
        "The ratio of $a$ to $b$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Write each algebraic expression as a verbal phrase."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x + 11$",
        "$4y - 3$",
        "$\\dfrac{n}{5}$",
        "$2(m + 7)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Write an expression for each real-world situation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "The cost of $t$ T-shirts at \\$15 each",
        "The number of inches in $f$ feet",
        "Maya's age if she is $4$ years younger than her brother, who \n is $b$ years old",
        "The amount left from \\$100 after spending $d$ dollars"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 2.3: Evaluating Expressions**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate each expression for $x = 5$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x + 12$",
        "$4x - 3$",
        "$x^2 - 6$",
        "$\\dfrac{x + 5}{2}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate each expression for $n = -3$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$n + 8$",
        "$2n - 5$",
        "$n^2$",
        "$-n^2$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate each expression for $a = 4$ and $b = -2$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$a + b$",
        "$a - b$",
        "$ab$",
        "$a^2 - b^2$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate each formula."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$A = \\ell w$ when $\\ell = 8$ and $w = 5$",
        "$P = 4s$ when $s = 6$",
        "$d = rt$ when $r = 50$ and $t = 3$",
        "$F = \\frac{9}{5}C + 32$ when $C = 15$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 2.4: Simplifying Expressions**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify by combining like terms."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$7x + 4x$",
        "$9y - 5y + 2$",
        "$3a + 5b - a + 2b$",
        "$4n^2 + 3n - 2n^2 + n$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use the distributive property to simplify."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$5(x + 3)$",
        "$-3(y - 4)$",
        "$4(2n + 1)$",
        "$-2(3m - 5)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify completely."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$3(x + 2) + 2x$",
        "$5(y - 1) - 3y$",
        "$4(2a + 3) - 2(a - 1)$",
        "$-(n + 4) + 3(n - 2)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\dfrac{1}{2}x + \\dfrac{3}{4}x$",
        "$\\dfrac{1}{3}(6y - 9)$",
        "$2(x^2 + 3x - 1) - (x^2 - 2x + 4)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Mixed Review**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For the expression $-2x^3 + 5x^2 - x + 7$:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "How many terms are there?",
        "What is the coefficient of $x^2$?",
        "What is the constant?",
        "Evaluate the expression when $x = 2$."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify, then evaluate for $x = 3$:\n\\[\n4(x + 2) - 2(x - 1)\n\\]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify, then evaluate for $y = -1$:\n\\[\n3y^2 + 5y - 2y^2 + 3y - 4\n\\]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A rectangle has length $(2x + 3)$ and width $(x + 1)$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Write an expression for the perimeter.",
        "Simplify the expression.",
        "Find the perimeter when $x = 4$."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Translate, simplify, and evaluate:\n\"Five more than twice a number, minus the number.\" Let the number \nbe $n = 7$."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Applications**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A phone plan costs \\$35 per month plus \\$0.05 per minute of calls."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Write an expression for the monthly cost if $m$ minutes are used.",
        "Find the cost for $200$ minutes.",
        "Find the cost for $500$ minutes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The formula for the area of a trapezoid is $A = \\frac{1}{2}(b_1 + b_2)h$, \nwhere $b_1$ and $b_2$ are the parallel bases and $h$ is the height."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Find the area when $b_1 = 6$, $b_2 = 10$, and $h = 4$.",
        "If $b_1 = x$, $b_2 = x + 4$, and $h = 6$, write and simplify \n an expression for the area."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A car rental company charges \\$40 per day plus \\$0.25 per mile."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Write an expression for the cost of renting for $d$ days and \n driving $m$ miles.",
        "Find the cost of a $3$-day rental with $150$ miles driven.",
        "Write and simplify an expression for the cost of renting the \n same car for two separate trips: one for $2$ days and $80$ miles, \n and another for $1$ day and $50$ miles."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Challenging Problems**"
    }
  ],
  "marginNotes": [
    {
      "type": "scripture",
      "reference": "Psalm 111:2",
      "text": "Great are the works of the Lord, studied \nby all who delight in them."
    }
  ]
}